SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Financial statement footnote 11 addresses uncertain tax positions. The plan administrator has analyzed the tax positions taken by the plan and has concluded there are no uncertain tax positions taken or expected to be taken that would require recognition of a liability (or asset) or disclosure in the financial statements.
On an annual basis, the board of trustees reviews and approves the Executive Administrator's performance and salary.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 11b
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Line 11b Explanation - All Trustees do not review the annual Form 990; however, the Administrator does review the Form 990 upon its completion prior to it being filed with the IRS. Additionally, the signing officer reviews prior to signing and submitting to the IRS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section B, line 15a
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Annually, the board of trustees reviews the job performance of the Fund's administrator, and through majority vote of the trustees, determines the compensation level for the administrator for the next fiscal year.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Section C, line 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: On an annual basis, the Fund has prepared the summary annual report (SAR) that is available to the general public. The SAR is available at the Fund office during normal business hours or upon request. Additionally, the annual audited financial statements are available for review upon request.

A committee has not been established to oversee the financial statement audit. The full board assumes responsibility for oversight of the audit and by majority vote, approves the plan auditors annually.
